<?xml version="1.0"?><h:html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2002/xforms" xmlns:ev="http://www.w3.org/2001/xml-events" xmlns:h="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:jr="http://openrosa.org/javarosa" xmlns:odk="http://www.opendatakit.org/xforms" xmlns:orx="http://openrosa.org/xforms" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"><h:head><h:title>OSCE B.sc Medical Sug._Administering an intradermal injection</h:title><model odk:xforms-version="1.0.0"><instance><data id="osce1_form" version="1.1"><intro><reserved_name_for_field_list_labels_3/><step1/><step2/><step3/><step4/><step5/><step6/><step7/><step8/><step9/><step10/><step11/><step12/><step13/><step14/><step15/><step16/><step17/><step18/><step19/><step20/><step21/><step22/><step23/><step24/><step25/><step26/><step27/><step28/><step29/><step30/><step31/></intro><meta><instanceID/></meta></data></instance><bind nodeset="/data/intro/reserved_name_for_field_list_labels_3" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step1" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step2" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step3" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step4" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step5" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step6" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step7" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step8" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step9" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step10" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step11" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step12" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step13" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step14" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step15" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step16" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step17" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step18" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step19" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step20" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step21" required="true()" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step22" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step23" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step24" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step25" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step26" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step27" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step28" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step29" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step30" type="string"/><bind nodeset="/data/intro/step31" type="string"/><bind jr:preload="uid" nodeset="/data/meta/instanceID" readonly="true()" type="string"/></model></h:head><h:body class="pages"><group appearance="field-list" ref="/data/intro"><select1 appearance="label" ref="/data/intro/reserved_name_for_field_list_labels_3"><label> </label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step1"><label>Goal: Appearance of a wheal at the site of injection.
Gather equipment. Check each medication order against the original physician's order according to agency policy. Clarify any inconsistencies. Check the patient's chart for allergies.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step2"><label>Know the actions, special nursing considerations, safe dose ranges, purpose of administration, and adverse effects of the medications to be administered. Consider the appropriateness of the medication for this patient.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step3"><label>Perform hand hygiene.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step4"><label>Move the medication cart to the outside of the patient's room or prepare for administration in the medication area.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step5"><label>Unlock the medication cart or drawer.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step6"><label>Prepare medications for one patient at a time.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step7"><label>Read the Medication order and select the proper medication from the patient's medication drawer or unit stock.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step8"><label>Compare the label with the Medication order. Check expiration dates and perform calculations, if necessary.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step9"><label>If necessary, withdraw medication from an ampule or vial.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step10"><label>Recheck the label with the Medication order before taking them to the patient.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step11"><label>Lock the medication cart before leaving it.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step12"><label>Transport medications to the patient's bedside carefully, and keep the medications in sight at all times.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step13"><label>Ensure that the patient receives the medications at the correct time.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step14"><label>Identify the patient. Usually, the patient should be identified using two methods. Compare information with the patient's chart- 
a. Check the name and identification number on the patient's identification band.
b. Ask the patient to state his or her name.
c. If the patient cannot identify him or herself, verify the patient's identification with a staff member who knows the patient for the second source.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step15"><label>Close the door to the room or pull the bedside curtain.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step16"><label>Complete necessary assessments before administering medications. Check allergy bracelet or ask patient about allergies. Explain the purpose and action of the medication to the patient.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step17"><label>Perform hand hygiene and put on clean gloves.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step18"><label>Select an appropriate administration site. Assist the patient to the appropriate position for the site chosen. Drape as needed to expose only area of site to be used.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step19"><label>Cleanse the site with an antimicrobial swab while wiping with a firm, circular motion and moving outward from the injection site. Allow the skin to dry</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step20"><label>Remove the needle cap with the non-dominant hand by pulling it straight off.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step21"><label>Use the non-dominant hand to spread the skin taut over the injection site.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step22"><label>Hold the syringe in the dominant hand, between the thumb and forefinger with the bevel of the needle up. .</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step23"><label>Hold the syringe at a 10- to 15-degree angle from the site. Place the needle almost flat against the patient's skin, bevel side up, and insert the needle into the skin so that the point of the needle can be seen through the skin. Insert the needle only about 1/8â€³ with entire bevel under the skin.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step24"><label>Once the needle is in place, steady the lower end of the syringe, and slide your dominant hand to the end of the plunger.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step25"><label>Slowly inject the agent while watching for a small wheal or blister to appear.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step26"><label>Withdraw the needle quickly at the same angle that it was inserted.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step27"><label>Do not massage area after removing needle. Tell the patient not to rub or scratch the site. If necessary, gently blot the site with a dry gauze square. Do not apply pressure or rub the site.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step28"><label>Do not recap the used needle. Engage the safety shield or needle guard, if present. Discard the needle and syringe in the appropriate receptacle.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step29"><label>Assist the patient to a position of comfort.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step30"><label>Remove gloves and dispose of them properly. Perform hand hygiene.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step31"><label>Observe the area for signs of a reaction at determined intervals after administration. Inform the patient of the need for inspection</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1></group></h:body></h:html>